Sentencas: Anode-supported solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with yttria-stabilized zirconia (YSZ) electrolytes were co-sintered at a temperature as low as 1250 degrees C, lower than the usual 1400 degrees C, by using 1 mol% Fe2O3 sintering aid.
Titulo: Effects of Reduced Firing Temperature on Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effect of sintering temperature on cell electrochemical performance was investigated for cells with two different composite cathodes: (LaasSr(0 2))(0 98)MnO3-delta (LSM) -YSZ or La0.6Sr0.4Fe0.8Co0.2O3 (LSCF) - Gd-doped Ceria (GDC).
Titulo: Effects of Reduced Firing Temperature on Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: For the latter case, the electrolyte included a 1.4-mu m-thick GDC layer that was co-sintered with the YSZ electrolyte and Ni-YSZ anode.
Titulo: Effects of Reduced Firing Temperature on Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Open-circuit voltages were near theoretical values for all cells.
Titulo: Effects of Reduced Firing Temperature on Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The LSM-cathode cell maximum power densities increased with decreasing sintering temperature, due to a decrease in anode polarization resistance.
Titulo: Effects of Reduced Firing Temperature on Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Cells with LSCF cathodes had substantially lower cathode polarization resistance and higher power density than the LSM cells.
Titulo: Effects of Reduced Firing Temperature on Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Energy-dispersive X-ray analysis did not detect GDC/YSZ interdiffusion or zirconate formation in the LSCF/GDC/YSZ region.
Titulo: Effects of Reduced Firing Temperature on Anode-Supported Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
